parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel quick disconnect can cause fuel to leak or spray, potentially leading to a fire hazard, especially when in close proximity to hot engine components.
symptoms: Fuel leaking or spraying from the fuel tank area
fuel pooling on the ground
strong gasoline odor
fuel dripping onto the front wheel or exhaust.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The stress fractures in the rear wheel flange can lead to complete failure of the part, causing vehicle damage and increasing the risk of loss of control.
symptoms: Stress fractures in 3 of 5 brake rotor mounting points
wheel mounts experiencing similar stress cracks.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS control module can cause the loss of ABS brakes, increasing the risk of a crash.
symptoms: Brake failure light comes on
no ABS brakes available
vehicle may experience abnormal braking behavior.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The excessive wear of the rubber in the brake chamber can cause the rear wheel to seize abnormally, leading to loss of control and accidents.
symptoms: Rear wheel seizes abnormally
rubber in brake chamber is severely worn
temporary correction of failure after cooling down.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended engagement of the front brakes can cause the front tire to lock up, leading to loss of control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: Front brakes engage and lock up the front tire
stopping the motorcycle in place
inability to move the motorcycle in traffic.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump can cause fuel leaks, which can lead to fires, accidents, or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Fuel odor
fuel leakage
split flange at the joint between the fuel pump output and the fuel line
fuel running down the front side of the motorcycle and exhaust header.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pressure control module can cause the vehicle to stall or leave the driver stranded, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Sudden failure of the fuel pressure control module without warning
leaving the driver stranded
vehicle stalling.
